Of the total purchases of the 3 products (widgets, doodads, and fizzbangs), which had the highest conversion from advertisement to purchase?  One could also use the profit margin to decide.
Determine if there is a correlation between the amount spent on marketing and the user exit from the sign up process. 
First, rank based on availability.  If there is no availability, you would not want it to show in results - at least, not at the beginning.  Then rank based on any user selected criteria in the session, such as proximity to attractions.  Then, rank on price.
Comparing average use time over the 3 year timeline and then to current usage would provide an indication as to whether use is atypical.  Seasonal differences in usage might be seen in patterns of usage over the timeline.
